 finished this quest in about 4 hours total playing time, which is great.  The price for selling this item use to be around 1500 now with the new quest it is down around 900.  I was 40 when I did this quest and I did it solo.  I know this is not a quest for Druids but it is a great way to make some quick cash if you do not mind going into areas where you will not gain any xp.  I also made around 100 pp in change (armor, weapon drops)<br>
<br>
<br>
Quest:<br>
1) Starts off in WK with Ryshon Hunsti (he is located along the shore in wk fairly close to the nk line.)  Hail him and then say 'I seek the sword of nobility'.  He will give you a lore no drop note. <br>
<br>
2) TP to butcherblock, go to the other side of the docks and look for Kanthuk Ogrebane.  Hail him then hand him the note.  The to finish this part say to him 'what strange image'.  He will tehn hand you a lore no drop necklace that is paladin only.<br>
<br>
3)  Get over to Dagnors Cauldron near the unrest zone.  you will find Llara.  Hail her hand her the necklace.  Then you say Who is Ruathey? You will recieve another lore no drop note.<br>
<br>
4) Go into unrest and wolf form up.  Go to the back of the mansion to the right side near where the gazebo is.  There are 3 ghouls/crazed ghouls that spawn in this area.  The can be kited or just rooted/dotted to kill.  These creatures drop small bronze and weapons as common loot.  The rare drop for the quest is a ghouls heart. (pos 815 neg 200).<br>
<br>
5)  Go into bb and run towards kaladiam.  Start tracking for crazed goblins.  These goblins spawn at a ruin site and there are 3 that spawn here.  They drop small ringmail, pp and the blade for the quest.  (pos 1500 neg 1500 obo)<br>
<br>
6)  TP to either nk or misty thicket and get up into HHK.  Go down to the warrior rooms and kill crazed goblins for the scroll.  (I never had to kill anything just buffed tanks with shield of spikes and regen and they had a hayday).<br>
<br>
7)  TP to lavastorm right next to the nek. forest and lavastorm entrance and meet Ruathey.  Hail her and give her the note you got from llara.  Then say what bag?  You will recieve a no drop lore bag.  You place the items you got within the bag.<br>
<br>
8)  Go within najena.  The hilt drops off any of the skeletons. once you have all 4 pieces then place in the bag and combine.<br>
<br>
Had alot of fun doing this quest since it was soo easy.  Also with all the bronze gear i got in unrest i was able to make me a dwarven paladin twink. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uligge.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ligge</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_ball.gif BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/4/01 11:43:59 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.eqguide.com/images/vermsmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Get ghoulsbane while you can before they nerf this...</span><hr size=1> Why would they nerf this?<br>
